sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K2036013
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: RBS-CII-TT-pRE-RBS-GFP-LVAtag, it is a GFP regulationary circuits. When CII is expressed it can further activate GFP and forming a Switching Lag-times.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Zhangyu Cheng
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: CII and pRE are a part of bactriaphage lambda operon.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: When CII is expressed it can further activate GFP and forming a Switching Lag-times. And in HUST-China 2016 designed circuit,this composite is constructed to test CII and pRE interaction.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K2036008
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: RBS-CIII-RBS-CIII,as Ftsh normally exists in E.coli to degrade CII, CIII functions as a inhibitor of Ftsh, and tandom expression of CIII,may enhance the effect on Ftsh
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Zhangyu Cheng
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: According to the Registry, prefix of other sequence are supposed to be "GAATTCGCGGCCGCTTCTAGAG" , so the scar produced by 3A assembly should be "TACTAGAG"

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K2036012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: RBS-CII-TT, CII is a regulatory gene derived from bacteriaphage lambda. It is an activate pRE's expression. And it can be normally degrade by Ftsh in E.coli.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Zhangyu Cheng
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: CII is an transcriptional activaor. One should add a related promoter downstream of CII.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K2036011
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: pRE-GFP-LVAtag, it is a GFP generator,and the production of GFP will be activated by CII and CIII.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Zhangyu Cheng
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: pRE comes from bacteriaphage lambda and GFP-LVAtag are standard part from Rgistry
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: One should put CII as an activator of pRE when constructing gene circuit.
